{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"7237","heading":"Priority placement, job placement, retraining, and counseling programs for United States Department of Energy employees affected by reduction in force","label":"7237 Priority placement, job placement, retraining, and counseling programs for United States Department of Energy employees affected by reduction in force","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch84/schVI/ptB","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationSection was enacted as part of the Energy and Water Development Appropriations Act, 1997, and not as part of the Department of Energy Organization Act which comprises this chapter."],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Definitions","label":"a Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"For the purposes of this section, the term “agency” means the United States Department of Energy.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fa%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a/2/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fa%2F2%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"regulations prescribed under ; orsection 3502 of title 5","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a/2/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fa%2F2%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"procedures established under ; orsection 3595 of title 5","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fa%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a/2/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fa%2F2%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an employee separated from service for cause on charges of misconduct or delinquency; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a/2/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/a/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fa%2F2%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an employee who, at the time of separation, meets the age and service requirements for an immediate annuity under subchapter III of chapter 83 or chapter 84 of title 5.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Priority placement and retraining program","label":"b Priority placement and retraining program","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 30 days after , the United States Department of Energy shall establish an agency-wide priority placement and retraining program for eligible employees.September 30, 1996","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Filling vacancy from outside agency","label":"c Filling vacancy from outside agency","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"there is then available any eligible employee who applies for the position within 30 days of the agency issuing a job announcement and is qualified (or can be trained or retrained to become qualified within 90 days of assuming the position) for the position; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the position is within the same commuting area as the eligible employee’s last-held position or residence.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Job placement and counseling services","label":"d Job placement and counseling services","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"career and personal counseling;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"training and job search skills; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/d/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7237/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7237%2Fd%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"job placement assistance, including assistance provided through cooperative arrangements with State and local employment services offices.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
